    <item>
      <title>How the Wicked Sons were Duped.</title>
      <link>https://stories.muthu.co/posts/fairy-tales-how-the-wicked-sons-were-duped/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://stories.muthu.co/posts/fairy-tales-how-the-wicked-sons-were-duped/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;figure class=&#34;&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;img-container&#34; style=&#34;--w: 728; --h: 1024;&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;img loading=&#34;lazy&#34; alt=&#34;Watercolor illustration of an elderly man with a long white beard, wearing a faded blue robe, sitting at a table surrounded by four younger men, his sons, dressed in similar robes but in shades of green, brown, red, and yellow. The sons are looking at him with disdainful expressions. The table is mostly bare. Soft, diffused lighting, watercolor paper texture visible.&#34; src=&#34;https://stories.muthu.co/posts/images/image_fairy-tales-how-the-wicked-sons-were-duped0.png&#34; width=&#34;728&#34; height=&#34;1024&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Once upon a time, there was a very rich old man. He thought he was about to say goodbye to the world, so he called his sons together and shared all his money and things with them. But guess what? He didn&amp;rsquo;t go anywhere for many years! And those years weren&amp;rsquo;t very happy ones. He was tired from being old, but even worse, his sons were not very nice to him. They were being mean and selfish!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Loving Laili</title>
