    <item>
      <title>Pride goeth before a Fall</title>
      <link>https://stories.muthu.co/posts/fairy-tales-pride-goeth-before-a-fall/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://stories.muthu.co/posts/fairy-tales-pride-goeth-before-a-fall/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;figure class=&#34;&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;img-container&#34; style=&#34;--w: 1024; --h: 974;&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;img loading=&#34;lazy&#34; alt=&#34;Watercolor illustration of ten cloth sellers, dressed in colorful fabrics, walking wearily through a dark, spooky forest. Three menacing robbers with exaggerated features leap from behind gnarled trees, brandishing crudely drawn swords and sticks. The cloth sellers look frightened and defenseless.&#34; src=&#34;https://stories.muthu.co/posts/images/image_fairy-tales-pride-goeth-before-a-fall0.png&#34; width=&#34;1024&#34; height=&#34;974&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Once upon a time, in a small village, lived ten cloth sellers who were best friends and always traveled together. One day, they went on a long trip to sell their beautiful fabrics and earned lots of money! As they headed back home, they had to pass through a thick, spooky forest. They didn&amp;rsquo;t know it, but three sneaky robbers lived in that forest!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
